From fef26d614ec445f45180afc4693ee8caa344443a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:37:28 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 17/48] Add warp.commands plugin API + command registry
 (oh-my-warp)

Plugins can register command-palette commands via warp.commands.register(id,
title, cb). The host registers the JS callback and sends RegisterCommandService
to the app, which records it in a global registry (app/src/plugin/commands.rs).
The callback returns a string shown as a toast when the command runs. Wires the
Phase-0 dead-code items (app_services, js_function_registry_mut,
plugin_service_caller) to real consumers. See PLUGIN_SPEC.md (M1).
